    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-13T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-13T12:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/7577: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-13T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 13, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 13—2:52 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Embassy has received a report that during an audience which the Secretary of
                    the Fascist Party in Albania had with the Duce<note n="6" xml:id="d598fn6"
                        >Benito Mussolini, Italian Prime Minister.</note> on January 9, the former
                    tendered his resignation. The Duce insisted, however, that the Secretary retain
                    his post adding that the present situation in Albania would soon undergo a
                    change for the better as the Germans had promised to extend military aid.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
